Name: Courier Corp
Description: DELISTED - Courier Corporation (Courier) is engaged in book manufacturing and specialty publishing. The Company operates in two business segments: book manufacturing and specialty publishing. The book manufacturing segment focuses on streamlining the process of bringing books from the point of creation to the point of use. It offers services from prepress and production through storage and distribution. Courier's book manufacturing markets are religious, educational and specialty trade books with products, including Bibles, educational textbooks and consumer books. The specialty publishing segment consists of Dover Publications, Inc. (Dover), Research & Education Association, Inc. (REA), and Federal Marketing Corporation, doing business as Creative Homeowner (Creative Homeowner). In May 2013, Courier Corp acquired FastPencil, Inc.
